Pongamos los puntos en un mapa

leaflet() %>% addTiles() %>% addCircles(data = Nothofagus, lat = ~latitude, 
    lng = ~longitude)
  • Otras opciones
    • addAwesomeMarkers
    • addCircleMarkers
    • addMarkers

Cambiemos el color segn especie

  • Nmero de especies
Number_spp <- Nothofagus$scrubbed_species_binomial %>% unique() %>% 
    length()
  • Nombre de especies
Spp_Names <- Nothofagus$scrubbed_species_binomial %>% unique()
  • Colores de colorbrewer2
Colores <- c("#a6cee3", "#1f78b4", "#b2df8a", "#33a02c", "#fb9a99", 
    "#e31a1c", "#fdbf6f", "#ff7f00", "#cab2d6")

Cambiemos el color segn especie (Cont.)

  • Creamos la paleta
pal <- colorFactor(Colores, domain = Spp_Names)
  • y finalmente el mapa
leaflet() %>% addTiles() %>% addCircles(data = Nothofagus, lat = ~latitude, 
    lng = ~longitude, color = ~pal(scrubbed_species_binomial), 
    fillOpacity = 0.5)

Genial tenemos las especies, pero cual es cual?

Labels

leaflet() %>% addTiles() %>% addCircles(data = Nothofagus, lat = ~latitude, 
    lng = ~longitude, color = ~pal(scrubbed_species_binomial), 
    fillOpacity = 0.5, label = ~scrubbed_species_binomial)

Popups

m <- leaflet() %>% addTiles() %>% addCircles(data = Nothofagus, 
    lat = ~latitude, lng = ~longitude, color = ~pal(scrubbed_species_binomial), 
    fillOpacity = 0.5, label = ~scrubbed_species_binomial, popup = ~datasource, 
    group = "Especies")
m
  • Podemos usar guardar en m para luego agregar cosas con %>%
  • agregamos Group Para control ms adelante

Leyenda

m <- m %>% addLegend(data = Nothofagus, "bottomright", pal = pal, 
    values = ~scrubbed_species_binomial, title = "Especies", 
    opacity = 1, group = "Leyenda")
m

Control de objetos

  • Ahora empezamos con los grupos!!
m <- m %>% addLayersControl(overlayGroups = c("Especies", "Leyenda"), 
    options = layersControlOptions(collapsed = TRUE))
m

Hagamos un grupo por especie

N_alpina <- Nothofagus %>% dplyr::filter(scrubbed_species_binomial == 
    "Nothofagus alpina")
leaflet() %>% addTiles() %>% addCircleMarkers(data = N_alpina, 
    lat = ~latitude, lng = ~longitude, color = ~pal(scrubbed_species_binomial), 
    fillOpacity = 0.5, label = ~scrubbed_species_binomial, popup = ~datasource)

Ahora para todas

Spp_Pres <- list()
for (i in 1:length(Spp_Names)) {
    Spp_Pres[[i]] <- Nothofagus %>% dplyr::filter(scrubbed_species_binomial == 
        Spp_Names[i])
}
names(Spp_Pres) <- Spp_Names

Generemos el mapa

Spp_Map <- leaflet() %>% addTiles() %>% addCircles(data = Spp_Pres[[1]], 
    lat = ~latitude, lng = ~longitude, color = ~pal(scrubbed_species_binomial), 
    fillOpacity = 0.5, label = ~scrubbed_species_binomial, popup = ~datasource, 
    group = Spp_Names[1]) %>% addCircles(data = Spp_Pres[[2]], 
    lat = ~latitude, lng = ~longitude, color = ~pal(scrubbed_species_binomial), 
    fillOpacity = 0.5, label = ~scrubbed_species_binomial, popup = ~datasource, 
    group = Spp_Names[2]) %>% addCircles(data = Spp_Pres[[3]], 
    lat = ~latitude, lng = ~longitude, color = ~pal(scrubbed_species_binomial), 
    fillOpacity = 0.5, label = ~scrubbed_species_binomial, popup = ~datasource, 
    group = Spp_Names[3])

En un loop

Spp_Map <- leaflet() %>% addTiles()
for (i in 1:length(Spp_Pres)) {
    Spp_Map <- Spp_Map %>% addCircles(data = Spp_Pres[[i]], lat = ~latitude, 
        lng = ~longitude, color = ~pal(scrubbed_species_binomial), 
        fillOpacity = 0.5, label = ~scrubbed_species_binomial, 
        popup = ~datasource, group = Spp_Names[i])
}

Agregemos leyenda

Spp_Map <- Spp_Map %>% addLegend(data = Nothofagus, "bottomright", 
    pal = pal, values = ~scrubbed_species_binomial, title = "Especies", 
    opacity = 1, group = "Leyenda")

Agregemos control por especie

Grupos <- c("Leyenda", Spp_Names)
Spp_Map <- Spp_Map %>% addLayersControl(overlayGroups = Grupos, 
    options = layersControlOptions(collapsed = TRUE)) %>% hideGroup("Leyenda")

Dudas?

Densidad por especie

Heat_Map <- leaflet() %>% addTiles()
for (i in 1:length(Spp_Pres)) {
    Heat_Map <- Heat_Map %>% addHeatmap(data = Spp_Pres[[i]], 
        lat = ~latitude, lng = ~longitude, group = Spp_Names[i])
}
Heat_Map <- Heat_Map %>% addLayersControl(baseGroups = Spp_Names, 
    options = layersControlOptions(collapsed = FALSE))

Polygonos

Ejemplo Regiones de Chile

download.file("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/derek-corcoran-barrios/derek-corcoran-barrios.github.io/master/Presentaciones_Espacial/Chile.zip", 
    destfile = "Chile.zip")
unzip("Chile.zip")
Chile <- read_sf("Chile.shp")
Chile_Spat <- Chile %>% as_Spatial()
Regiones_Chile <- leaflet() %>% addTiles() %>% addPolygons(data = Chile_Spat, 
    fillColor = topo.colors(16, alpha = NULL), weight = 0.5, 
    label = ~NAME_1, group = "Regiones") %>% addLayersControl(overlayGroups = "Regiones", 
    options = layersControlOptions(collapsed = TRUE))

Ejemplo Regiones de Chile

Regiones_Chile

Agreguemos medidas de reas

Regiones_Chile <- Regiones_Chile %>% addMeasurePathToolbar(options = measurePathOptions(imperial = F, 
    minPixelDistance = 100, showDistances = FALSE))

Y si quieremos generar nuevas reas?

Regiones_Chile <- leaflet() %>% addTiles() %>% addPolygons(data = Chile_Spat, 
    fillColor = topo.colors(16, alpha = NULL), weight = 0.5, 
    label = ~NAME_1, group = "Regiones") %>% addDrawToolbar(targetGroup = "Regiones Marinas", 
    editOptions = editToolbarOptions(selectedPathOptions = selectedPathOptions())) %>% 
    addLayersControl(overlayGroups = c("Regiones", "Regiones Marinas"), 
        options = layersControlOptions(collapsed = TRUE)) %>% 
    addMeasurePathToolbar(options = measurePathOptions(imperial = F, 
        minPixelDistance = 100, showDistances = FALSE))

Editar estilos

Regiones_Chile <- Regiones_Chile %>% addStyleEditor()

Mapa final

download.file("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/derek-corcoran-barrios/derek-corcoran-barrios.github.io/master/Presentaciones_Espacial/Chile.zip", 
    destfile = "Chile.zip")
unzip("Chile.zip")
Chile <- read_sf("Chile.shp")
Chile_Spat <- Chile %>% as_Spatial()
Regiones_Chile <- leaflet() %>% addTiles() %>% addPolygons(data = Chile_Spat, 
    fillColor = topo.colors(16, alpha = NULL), weight = 0.5, 
    label = ~NAME_1, group = "Regiones") %>% addDrawToolbar(targetGroup = "Regiones Marinas", 
    editOptions = editToolbarOptions(selectedPathOptions = selectedPathOptions())) %>% 
    addLayersControl(overlayGroups = c("Regiones", "Regiones Marinas"), 
        options = layersControlOptions(collapsed = TRUE)) %>% 
    addMeasurePathToolbar(options = measurePathOptions(imperial = F, 
        minPixelDistance = 100, showDistances = FALSE)) %>% addStyleEditor()
